Untitled 1.text: There are two types of pessimisms in the discursive tradition: psychological pessimism and transcendental pessimism.

Untitled 2.text: These types of pessimisms are distinct in kind.

Untitled 3.text: Transcendental pessimism is philosophical in kind.

Untitled 4.text: Psychological pessimism is not philosophical in kind.

Untitled 5.text: We should only adhere to the standards and framework of transcendental pessimism when we attempt pessimistic arguments in philosophical practice.
